ns and suddenly stops it might be because of your logic board.";i:54;s:60:"The logic board receives and responds signals to any remote.";i:55;s:110:"You might need to consider replacing it if your door is not working properly or you may purchase a new opener.";i:56;s:105:"If the garage door opens correctly but fails to close completely there may be one of three common causes.";i:57;s:42:"The close-limit switch may need adjusting.";i:58;s:131:"Your garage door has set-limit switches that instruct the motor when to stop runningboth when it is opening and when it is closing.";i:59;s:216:"I do not want to be like Sam and be a pain in the ass to every other driver in this street and I am looking for any idea to be able to remotelyautomatically open the door when getting close like 150-200m to my house.";i:60;s:79:"You can assume that once the house knows I am approaching it can open the door.";}}